@layout DogAdoptionWebsite.Components.Layout.MainLayout
@page "/our success stories"

<style>
    body {
        background-color: #FFF9E3; /* Pale pastel yellow */
        color: #333333; /* Dark gray for text */
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 32px;
        text-align: center;
        color: #b5651d; /* Brick color */
        font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
        margin-top: 20px;
        text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    .resource-container {
        background-color: #FFF4DB; /* Softer pastel background for the section */
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        opacity: 0.6;
        transition: 0.3s;
    }

    .resource-container:hover {opacity: 1}

    .resource-container p {
            margin-top: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: #000000;
    }

    .resource-container h4 {
        color: #636B2F; 
    }

    
</style>
<h1>Our Success Stories</h1>

<div class="resource-container">
    <h4>
        Buddy's Second Chance
        <p> Buddy, a two-year-old Golden Retriever mix, 
            was rescued from a shelter where he had spent 
            over six months waiting for a home. His boundless 
            energy and love for fetch caught the eye of the 
            Johnson family. Now, Buddy spends his days playing 
            in their backyard with the kids and cuddling on the 
            couch during movie nights. The Johnsons say adopting 
            Buddy brought joy and laughter back into their home.</p>
    </h4>
</div>





<div class="resource-container">
    <h4>
        Luna the Therapy Dog
        <p>
            Luna, a gentle Labrador, was overlooked because of her 
            shy nature. That changed when she met Sarah, a retired 
            teacher looking for a companion. Sarah worked patiently 
            to build Luna's confidence, and in return, Luna became 
            a comforting presence for Sarah’s volunteer work at a 
            local hospital. Luna now brings smiles to patients every 
            week, proving that love and patience can transform a timid 
            dog into a hero.
        </p>
    </h4>
</div>







<div class="resource-container">
    <h4>
        Max's New Adventures
        <p>
            Max, a spirited Jack Russell Terrier, had a history of being 
            returned to the shelter due to his high energy. Enter Mark, 
            an avid hiker and runner. The two quickly became inseparable 
            adventure buddies, conquering trails and exploring nature 
            together. Max found his perfect match in Mark, and the pair 
            now shares an Instagram account chronicling their adventures.
        </p>
    </h4>
</div>





<div class="resource-container">
    <h4>
        Heroic Scout
        <p>
            Scout, a German Shepherd, was adopted by firefighter James after 
            being deemed "too active" by previous owners. During a family camping 
            trip, Scout alerted everyone to a fire that had started nearby, 
            potentially saving lives. Scout has since earned the title of 
            "family hero" and enjoys endless belly rubs and treats as a reward.
        </p>
    </h4>
</div>
